song_name: At Least My Heart Was Open

version_description: Easy and fun song, wrote the chords according to the "Live in London" version and his other live performances. In the intro, play the first line of chords, then play G and G6 in shuffle rhythm for a while, occasionally throwing in a G7. In the verses, play G and G6 in shuffle rhythm where 'G' is noted. Do the same thing with C and C6 where 'C' is noted. In the chorus, play normal Em and C while keeping the shuffle pattern with the G.
My version is uses Drop D (the tuning Foy Vance uses). I also added the Chords that Foy Vance uses.

To play it exactly like him, tune your guitar to D standard and play the chords below. If you want to play in E standard, transpose -2 and play those chords or put a capo on the third fret and transpose -5.
Chords for the original studio version from Foy Vance.
